  "issue_title": "Bug: noise in stdout interfere json parsing",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nUnder `--json` (or `--json-output`), several CLI commands print non-fatal warnings to stdout, ahead of or alongside the JSON payload. Any consumer using `jq`, `python -m json.tool`, or shell parsing fails with a JSON parse error the moment one of these warning paths fires.\n\nThere is a common pattern which is used by many popular applications (`gh`, `kubectl` etc), which makes you print to the `stdout` only actual results. The rest (logs, warnings, loading bars etc) goes to the `stderr`. Such pattern is partially used in `gitt`, but far not everywhere. I think we should just standardize it across the whole codebase.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. `gitt issues list --json | jq`\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nJSON parsed successfully\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nFails to parse JSON",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-08T21:59:41.000Z",
